    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e9267baf_039f1e80",
        "filename": "milo/api/config/project.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-12T00:36:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also considering: removing column and let the renderer do all the layout automatically.  Such that header becomes just a long list of entries.  Not sure if that\u0027s doable though.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "5c1bbf3c067ba443b5b852bbac2a7fa33634bd90",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "070d11eb_62b8220e",
        "filename": "milo/api/config/project.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1154295
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-12T01:03:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s probably do-able to use some heuristic to \"balance\" out the columns, but I don\u0027t think it\u0027ll ever turn out as nice as just letting the user have full control over the layout. Different projects have different requirements, and I think we would benefit from having more layout options. That also makes the rendering itself much more straight-forward. :)",
      "parentUuid": "e9267baf_039f1e80",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "5c1bbf3c067ba443b5b852bbac2a7fa33634bd90",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7220d031_d825d37d",
        "filename": "milo/api/config/project.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-12T16:04:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think it is doable and it would simplify this proto and prevent users from having arbitrary orders of entry types, e.g. oncall after links or vice versa, or oncall, then link, then oncall again. Also this config proto currently allows arbitrary number of columns and putting console_groups to the left from oncalls. Do we really need such flexibility/generality? I don\u0027t think we have this requirement / users care.\n\nConsider squashing Column and Entry into Header, so that Header is simply\n\nmessage Header {\n    Oncall oncall \u003d 1;\n    Links links \u003d 2;\n    ConsoleSummaryGroup console_groups \u003d 3;\n}\n\nthen we can render it with predefined order:\n\n  link1            CONSOLE SUMMARY GOES HERE\n  link2            CONSOLE SUMMARY GOES HERE\n  link3            CONSOLE SUMMARY GOES HERE \n  oncall1          CONSOLE SUMMARY GOES HERE\n  oncall2          CONSOLE SUMMARY GOES HERE\n  oncall3          CONSOLE SUMMARY GOES HERE",
      "parentUuid": "070d11eb_62b8220e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "5c1bbf3c067ba443b5b852bbac2a7fa33634bd90",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "86e387e6_4539c381",
        "filename": "milo/api/config/project.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-13T19:23:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the arbitrary column requirement was inspired by this console:\nhttps://build.chromium.org/p/client.v8/console\n\nWhich uses 3 columns instead of 2, in an attempt to make the header a bit flatter.  I think I like constraining the layout options to make the configuration more straightforward (ie nodir\u0027s suggestion).  I\u0027ll try that out.  Michael what do you think?",
      "parentUuid": "7220d031_d825d37d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "5c1bbf3c067ba443b5b852bbac2a7fa33634bd90",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a25e4a7c_85f62537",
        "filename": "milo/api/config/project.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1154295
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-13T20:09:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m of the opinion that we should err on the side of customization. With that said, if you feel that there aren\u0027t enough actual use-cases for that to justify the complexity in configuration, then constraining it in this manner sounds good to me. I can\u0027t say I know enough about how useful this is in practice to have a strong opinion.",
      "parentUuid": "86e387e6_4539c381",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "5c1bbf3c067ba443b5b852bbac2a7fa33634bd90",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
